Commentary Text: U Yadav to Samson, out Caught by Moeen Ali!! Two in two for Umesh. His third wicket of the match, he's on a roll in the past few games. Getting better with every game. Bowls a gentle length delivery first up and Samson flicks it straight to the man at short mid-wicket. A soft dismissal, indeed. Scored 90-odd against RCB earlier in the tournament, walks back for a duck today. Samson c Moeen Ali b U Yadav 0(1)

Commentary Text: U Yadav to Rahane, out Lbw!! The impact was marginal but enough to go against Rahane. It was the off-cutter outside off, Rahane moved inside and went for a wild heave. Got beaten and was struck on the pads. The umpire took his time to give his decision but in the end he's right. So, finally Rahane' struggle comes to an end. Might be a blessing in disguise for the Royals. They need someone who can strike the ball well. Rahane lbw b U Yadav 33(31) [4s-3]

Commentary Text: Shreyas Gopal to de Villiers, out Stumped!! Game. Set. Match. That is a hugeeeeeeee wicket. The googly is misread. Looks to drive and misses it. Commentary Text: Gowtham to Kohli, out Bowled!! Kohli is bowled to a spinner. Seen that so often in this IPL. I can recollect Mujeeb, Rashid and now Gowtham. The bowler does a cool fist pump to celebrate the wicket. Kohli knew he had to do something against Gowtham, struggled in the first over, and decided to step out, but cleverly bowled by Gowtham, going wide of the crease and darting in a fast offie, which breaks in through the bat-pad gap to take Kohli's off stump out. They check for the no-ball on the side crease, but Gowtham had his leg up in the air and didn't land. A body blow to RCB. Kohli b Gowtham 4(9)
